{{see|Xerox}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈziɹ.ɑks/}}
*Schoolbook Phonetics: (zērʹäks)
*Last Resort Phonetics: ZEER-ox

===Etymology===
From '''Xerox'''™, the trademark name for a type of [[photocopier]], via ''[[xerography]]'' from Greek ''xero'' meaning dry and ''graphy'' meaning writing

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# {{slang}} A [[photocopy]].
#:* Hand me that '''xerox''', would you?

====Usage notes====
According to Xerox Corporation, ''Xerox''® is properly used only as a brand name to identify the company’s products and services, for instance “a Xerox printer”.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|xerox|es}}

# {{slang}} To make a paper [[copy]] or copies by means of a [[photocopier]].
#:* I '''xeroxed''' the report for all the people at the meeting.

====Usage notes====
The Xerox trademark is at risk of becoming generic because of this use. The company is engaged in an ongoing campaign to convince the public that Xerox should not be used as a verb.

